  &lt;div class=&quot;article-hero&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;nakshatra-num&quot;&gt;Nakshatra 01 of 27&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Ashwini Nakshatra&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p class=&quot;subtitle&quot;&gt;The First Star — Swift, Healing &amp;amp; New Beginnings&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;table class=&quot;quick-ref&quot;&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Detail&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Information&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Zodiac Sign (Rasi)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Aries (Mesha) — 0° to 13°20&#39;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Ruling Planet&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Ketu&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Presiding Deity&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Ashwini Kumaras (Divine Healers)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Symbol&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Horse&#39;s Head&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Gana&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Deva (Divine)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Nadi&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Vata&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Quality (Guna)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Rajas&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Beeja Mantra&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Om Ashwinyai Namah (ఓం అశ్వినీ నమః)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Who Are the Ashwini Kumaras?&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Ashwini Nakshatra is presided over by the &lt;strong&gt;Ashwini Kumaras&lt;/strong&gt; — the twin divine physicians of the gods. In Vedic mythology, they are the sons of the Sun god (Surya) and are known for their extraordinary healing powers, speed and youthful vitality. They ride golden horses and are always ready to help those in need.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Just like the Ashwini Kumaras who rush to heal and help, people born under this Nakshatra carry an innate desire to initiate, heal and lead the way for others.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div class=&quot;highlight-box&quot;&gt;
    &quot;Ashwini is the spark that starts the fire — the first breath of a new dawn. It is the energy of pure beginning, untouched by hesitation.&quot;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Key Traits of Ashwini Nakshatra&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;As the very first of the 27 Nakshatras, Ashwini carries the energy of fresh starts, courage and movement. People born under this star are naturally fast-thinking, action-oriented and independent.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h3&gt;Positive Qualities&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;ul class=&quot;remedy-list&quot;&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Naturally courageous and bold — first to act in any situation&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Quick thinkers with sharp instincts&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Strong healing ability — natural doctors, therapists and helpers&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic, youthful energy that never seems to age&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Independent nature — love to initiate new projects&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Deeply loyal to family and close ones&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Athletic and physically active by nature&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;h3&gt;Challenges to Watch&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;ul class=&quot;remedy-list&quot;&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Can be impulsive — act before thinking&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Restlessness — difficulty sitting still or waiting&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;May start many things but struggle to finish&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Impatience can cause friction in relationships&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Tendency to be headstrong and resist advice&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;The Four Padas (Quarters)&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;pada-grid&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;pada-card&quot;&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;1st Pada — Aries Navamsa&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Ruled by Mars. Extra fire, leadership and courage. Very action-oriented and competitive. Natural born leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;pada-card&quot;&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;2nd Pada — Taurus Navamsa&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Ruled by Venus. More grounded and practical. Combines speed with stability. Good at building wealth and comfort.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;pada-card&quot;&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;3rd Pada — Gemini Navamsa&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Ruled by Mercury. Sharp intellect and communication skills. Quick wit, love for learning and versatile talents.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;pada-card&quot;&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;4th Pada — Cancer Navamsa&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Ruled by Moon. More emotional and caring. Strong intuition and deep attachment to home and family.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Career &amp;amp; Life Path&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Ashwini natives thrive in careers that involve &lt;strong&gt;speed, healing and initiation&lt;/strong&gt;. They are not made for slow, routine desk jobs — they need movement, challenge and variety.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;ul class=&quot;remedy-list&quot;&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Medicine, Surgery, Alternative Healing, Physiotherapy&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Sports, Athletics, Martial Arts, Adventure&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Military, Police, Emergency Services&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurship — starting new ventures&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Travel, Racing, Logistics&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Veterinary Science (connection to horses)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Love &amp;amp; Relationships&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;In relationships, Ashwini natives are passionate, spontaneous and deeply loyal once committed. However, their impatient nature means they need a partner who can keep up with their energy and give them space to be independent. They fall in love quickly but also need freedom.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;They are most compatible with &lt;strong&gt;Shatabhisha and Punarvasu&lt;/strong&gt; Nakshatras.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Health Tendencies&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Since Ashwini governs the &lt;strong&gt;head and brain&lt;/strong&gt;, natives may be prone to headaches, migraines and head injuries. The restless energy of Ketu can also cause nervous system sensitivity. Regular meditation and physical exercise help balance this energy tremendously.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;Remedies &amp;amp; Spiritual Practices&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;ul class=&quot;remedy-list&quot;&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Chant: &lt;strong&gt;Om Ashwinyai Namah&lt;/strong&gt; — 108 times daily&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Worship the Ashwini Kumaras on Sundays&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Offer prayers to Lord Ganesha to remove obstacles&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Wear &lt;strong&gt;Cat&#39;s Eye (Lehsunia)&lt;/strong&gt; gemstone after consulting an astrologer&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Donate medicines or support medical causes — aligns with healing energy&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Practice early morning exercise — sunrise energy matches Ashwini perfectly&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;div class=&quot;highlight-box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;strong&gt;Ashwini&#39;s life lesson:&lt;/strong&gt; Learn to slow down and finish what you start. Your speed is your gift — your patience will be your mastery.
  &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- end English --&gt;


