the entry point for positive, spiritual vibrations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Why the North-East Matters:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,0,0&quot;&gt;Clarity of Mind:&lt;/b&gt; Keeping this corner clean and open ensures that the residents experience mental peace and clear decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,1,0&quot;&gt;The &quot;7&quot; Perspective:&lt;/b&gt; As a Number 7 seeker, I often find that people with a blocked North-East corner feel a &quot;spiritual fog&quot;—my intuition helps me identify these subtle energy blocks that traditional layouts might miss.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,2,0&quot;&gt;Practical Tip for Modern Homes:&lt;/b&gt; If you are in a condo or house where you cannot move walls, simply placing a bowl of clean water or a small plant in the North-East can significantly shift the energy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;The Result:&lt;/b&gt; When we align our physical space with these cosmic &quot;sutras,&quot; we stop fighting against our environment and start flowing with it.&lt;/p&gt;</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/5016171860168182213'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/5016171860168182213'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.valabhiastrology.com/2026/01/the-north-east-corner-inviting-divine.html' title='The North-East Corner: Inviting Divine Energy into Your Home'/><author><name>Siri</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/06162536254033727217</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='31' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiSFT4D-0zHGxTtPMCDHJ1VLGh94BmXq_OuI8lT75pd9Z1ER45kxeJZqlrlA3p6ZgL6dzqOaGvJkG11FQaQoyTB4FnkuQe2yt5aUqnKovgkgbDkOmnloNfGudoBc_6zGVG4QA0hxvZ9EA4h1eNxSEJfCZoXBwH3TFjTjoRmuDvQgoIcag/s220/febn75jb.png'/></author></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7610569779982788138.post-1119293929568709618</id><published>2026-01-10T06:13:00.000-08:00</published><updated>2026-01-10T06:13:44.958-08:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Planets"/><title type='text'>Shani’s Wisdom: Embracing the Discipline of Karma</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: large;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Shani Sutra: The Great Teacher of Karma&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,1&quot;&gt;In Vedic Astrology, &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;20&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,1&quot;&gt;Shani (Saturn)&lt;/b&gt; is often misunderstood. While many fear his gaze, he is actually the &quot;Great Teacher&quot; who ensures we stay on our true path.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,2&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,2&quot;&gt;The Lesson of Time:&lt;/b&gt;
Saturn teaches us that true success is built through patience and persistence. He governs the &quot;Sutras&quot; of reality—reminding us that every action has an equal and opposite reaction.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,3&quot;&gt;The &quot;7&quot; Connection:&lt;/b&gt;
For those of us born under the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;51&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,3&quot;&gt;Number 7&lt;/b&gt;, Saturn provides the grounding we need. While our ruling planet Ketu pulls us toward the mystical and spiritual, Saturn ensures we remain disciplined enough to share that wisdom with the world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6,4&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6,4&quot;&gt;Embracing the Grind:&lt;/b&gt;
If you are facing delays in your life, do not be discouraged. Shani is simply asking you to refine your work and strengthen your foundation. When the timing is finally right, the rewards he gives are permanent.&lt;/p&gt;</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/1119293929568709618'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/1119293929568709618'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.valabhiastrology.com/2026/01/shanis-wisdom-embracing-discipline-of.html' title='Shani’s Wisdom: Embracing the Discipline of Karma'/><author><name>Siri</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/06162536254033727217</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='31' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiSFT4D-0zHGxTtPMCDHJ1VLGh94BmXq_OuI8lT75pd9Z1ER45kxeJZqlrlA3p6ZgL6dzqOaGvJkG11FQaQoyTB4FnkuQe2yt5aUqnKovgkgbDkOmnloNfGudoBc_6zGVG4QA0hxvZ9EA4h1eNxSEJfCZoXBwH3TFjTjoRmuDvQgoIcag/s220/febn75jb.png'/></author></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7610569779982788138.post-478859283604147869</id><published>2026-01-09T08:06:00.000-08:00</published><updated>2026-01-09T08:06:31.260-08:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Vastu"/><title type='text'>Vastu Shastra: Bringing Your Home into Divine Balance</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your home is more than just walls and a roof; it is a living entity that breathes with you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;92&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;13&quot;&gt;Vastu Shastra&lt;/b&gt; is the ancient &quot;Sutra&quot; of architecture that ensures your living space is a source of energy, not a drain on it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;14&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;14&quot;&gt;The Foundation of Vastu:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;15&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;15,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;15,0,0&quot;&gt;The Five Elements:&lt;/b&gt; Vastu balances Earth, Water, Fire, Air, and Space within your four walls.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;15,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;15,1,0&quot;&gt;Directional Flow:&lt;/b&gt; From the entrance to the kitchen, every direction carries a specific planetary vibration that affects your health and prosperity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;15,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;15,2,0&quot;&gt;Vastu in Toronto:&lt;/b&gt; Even in modern Canadian homes, we can use simple Vedic adjustments to remove blockages and invite peace into our families.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;16&quot;&gt;Aligning your home is the first step toward aligning your life.&lt;/p&gt;</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/478859283604147869'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/478859283604147869'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.valabhiastrology.com/2026/01/vastu-shastra-bringing-your-home-into.html' title='Vastu Shastra: Bringing Your Home into Divine Balance'/><author><name>Siri</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/06162536254033727217</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='31' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiSFT4D-0zHGxTtPMCDHJ1VLGh94BmXq_OuI8lT75pd9Z1ER45kxeJZqlrlA3p6ZgL6dzqOaGvJkG11FQaQoyTB4FnkuQe2yt5aUqnKovgkgbDkOmnloNfGudoBc_6zGVG4QA0hxvZ9EA4h1eNxSEJfCZoXBwH3TFjTjoRmuDvQgoIcag/s220/febn75jb.png'/></author></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7610569779982788138.post-6450087782203331375</id><published>2026-01-09T08:05:00.000-08:00</published><updated>2026-01-09T08:05:35.996-08:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Muhurtha"/><title type='text'>The Power of Timing: Why Muhurtha is the Secret to Success</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the Vedic tradition, we believe that &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;40&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Time is the King&lt;/b&gt;. Even the best intentions can fail if the timing is out of sync with the universe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;Why Timing Matters:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,0,0&quot;&gt;Cosmic Alignment:&lt;/b&gt; Muhurtha is the science of choosing a moment when the planetary energies are in total harmony with your goal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,1,0&quot;&gt;Syncing with Your Chart:&lt;/b&gt; It is not enough to find a &quot;good day&quot; on a calendar; the time must specifically sync with your personal birth chart to ensure a perfect outcome.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7,2,0&quot;&gt;The Seed Principle:&lt;/b&gt; Just as a seed planted in the right season thrives, a project started at the right Muhurtha carries the energy of success from its very first second.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;Whether it is a &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;16&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;Griha Pravesh&lt;/b&gt;, a wedding, or a new business, don&#39;t just start—start when the stars are on your side.&lt;/p&gt;</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/6450087782203331375'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/6450087782203331375'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.valabhiastrology.com/2026/01/the-power-of-timing-why-muhurtha-is.html' title='The Power of Timing: Why Muhurtha is the Secret to Success'/><author><name>Siri</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/06162536254033727217</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='31' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiSFT4D-0zHGxTtPMCDHJ1VLGh94BmXq_OuI8lT75pd9Z1ER45kxeJZqlrlA3p6ZgL6dzqOaGvJkG11FQaQoyTB4FnkuQe2yt5aUqnKovgkgbDkOmnloNfGudoBc_6zGVG4QA0hxvZ9EA4h1eNxSEJfCZoXBwH3TFjTjoRmuDvQgoIcag/s220/febn75jb.png'/></author></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-7610569779982788138.post-7411460098708087130</id><published>2026-01-09T06:44:00.000-08:00</published><updated>2026-01-09T06:44:41.833-08:00</updated><category scheme="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#" term="Planets"/><title type='text'>Chandra Sutra: Why the Moon is the Key to Your Intuition</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot;&gt;The Message:&lt;/b&gt; In Vedic Astrology, your Moon sign is more important than your Sun sign. &lt;span class=&quot;citation-1&quot;&gt;It represents your mind (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;111&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot;&gt;Manas&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-1 citation-end-1&quot;&gt;) and how you feel the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In Vedic Astrology, while your Sun sign represents your ego, the &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;65&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Moon (Chandra)&lt;/b&gt; represents your mind and soul. It is the mirror that reflects your inner world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;The Mind-Moon Connection&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;The Moon governs our emotions, our subconscious, and our sense of peace. In the &quot;Simple&quot; theme of life, if your Moon is balanced, your path feels clear. If it is unsettled, no amount of logic can fix the feeling of being lost.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;Why the Moon Matters to a &quot;Number 7&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;Since I am a &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;13&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;Number 7&lt;/b&gt; ruled by Ketu, I have learned that my intuition is directly tied to the lunar cycles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;8,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;8,0,0&quot;&gt;The New Moon:&lt;/b&gt; A time for the &quot;7&quot; seeker to go inward and retreat.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;8,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;8,1,0&quot;&gt;The Full Moon:&lt;/b&gt; A time when our psychic &quot;Number 7&quot; sensitivity is at its highest peak.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;9&quot;&gt;Living by the Lunar Rhythm&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;To navigate your &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;17&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;Cosmic Sutra&lt;/b&gt;, you must watch the Moon. It is the fastest-moving &quot;Graha,&quot; changing signs every 2.5 days, bringing new emotional &quot;threads&quot; for us to weave into our day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-1 citation-end-1&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;11&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;11&quot;&gt;Are you feeling the pull of the current Moon? Check your chart and see which house Chandra is illuminating today.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;11&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/7411460098708087130'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='https://www.blogger.com/feeds/7610569779982788138/posts/default/7411460098708087130'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='https://www.valabhiastrology.com/2026/01/chandra-sutra-why-moon-is-key-to-your.html' title='Chandra Sutra: Why the Moon is the Key to Your Intuition'/><author><name>Siri</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/06162536254033727217</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='31' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiSFT4D-0zHGxTtPMCDHJ1VLGh94BmXq_OuI8lT75pd9Z1ER45kxeJZqlrlA3p6ZgL6dzqOaGvJkG11FQaQoyTB4FnkuQe2yt5aUqnKovgkgbDkOmnloNfGudoBc_6zGVG4QA0hxvZ9EA4h1eNxSEJfCZoXBwH3TFjTjoRmuDvQgoIcag/s220/febn75jb.png'/></author></entry></feed>